{"timestamp": "2026-06-24T17:45:06.965799", "direction": "JD_BUILDER_INPUT", "identifier": "raw_text_received", "data": "\n\n===== PAGE 1 =====\n\n100%\n\nJob Title: Business Analyst \u2013 Entry Level\nDesignation: Junior Business Analyst\nLocation: Pune, India\nDepartment: Business Strategy & Analytics\nCompany: InsightEdge Consulting Pvt. Ltd.\nAbout Company:\nInsightEdge Consulting, founded in 2016, provides business consulting and analytics services to\nretail, healthcare, and finance clients across India and Southeast Asia. With 300+ professionals,\nwe combine data, strategy, and technology to drive digital transformation.\nJob Summary:\nWe are seeking fresh graduates eager to kickstart their careers in business analysis. You will\nwork closely with senior analysts to gather requirements, analyze data, and deliver insights that\ninfluence strategic decisions.\nKey Responsibilities:\n- Assist in gathering and documenting business requirements.\n- Analyze business processes and suggest improvements.\n- Create dashboards and reports for client stakeholders.\n- Support senior analysts in preparing presentations.\n- Conduct competitor and market research.\nRequired Technical Skills:\n- Excel/Google Sheets proficiency.\n- Knowledge of SQL (preferred).\n- Exposure to BI tools like Power BI or Tableau.\n- Familiarity with Agile/Scrum methodologies.\n\n===== PAGE 2 =====\n\n\nSoft Skills:\n- Analytical and logical reasoning.\n- Strong communication and documentation.\n- Curiosity and eagerness to learn.\n- Collaboration and teamwork.\nPreferred Qualifications:\n- Bachelor's degree in Business, Economics, or IT.\n- Internship experience in analytics or consulting.\nWorking Model:\nOnsite, with hybrid flexibility after 6 months.\nWhat We Offer:\n- Mentorship by senior business analysts.\n- Structured training programs.\n- Career growth opportunities.\n- Medical insurance and team outings.\nApplication Process:\n- Aptitude test.\n- Case study exercise.\n- Technical + HR interview."}
